Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: The complex was constructed in 2016 in the northeast area of Dieppe, this high-income area has experienced a steady growth of new residential and commercial construction, including mixed-use development with hotels, stores, shops, restaurants and services. The property is situated on 2.92 acres of land and offers approximately 14,820 square feet of gross leasable area, of which approximately 7,689 square feet is vacant. The building has 14-foot clear ceiling heights, which can easily accommodate a variety of office, retail and light industrial uses. The site also includes approximately 1 acre of excess, undeveloped land for future building expansion.

Rare opportunity in this unique and easily identifiable building located in beautiful Downtown Dieppe. Local area attractions include the Dieppe Farmer's Market, the Wingate hotel, the Cultural Arts Centre, Dieppes Public Library and Place 1604. Retailers nearby include Maddie and Sofia, Copper Branch, Ton's Bistro, and Uni Financial Cooperation.

Terrasses du Marché, is the newest mixed-use community development currently under construction by DuParc Real Estate Group, located in the heart of the beautiful Downtown Dieppe. Inspired by the vibrant community, this development will consist of residential, retail and office space.

Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: Ideally located on Champlain Street in the growing, vibrant and popular Downtown Dieppe. 200 Champlain is nestled into the streetscape of Downtown Dieppe where you will become neighbors with well-established local restaurants, and services. Within the complex you will find the National Bank, Service New Brunswick, Bohème, Vienneau Insurance, La Place and many more. The property is located within walking distance from Place 1604, City Hall, Dieppe’s Farmers Market and major transit stops. Not only is Downtown Dieppe easily accessible by transit, there are a number of surface and street parking options nearby and is very walkable from surrounding neighborhoods. Downtown Dieppe’s popularity is soaring with many new multi-residential and mixed-use buildings now complete with future development showing no signs of slowing. Now is a great time to take advantage of this prime retail opportunity and become part of the excitement in Downtown Dieppe. See the flyer for more!
Newly renovated space in 2018 perfect for a restaurant in a prime ground floor corner unit. See flyer for details!

438 Paul Street provides an unmatched opportunity for small or larger tenants in a centrally located retail strip mall. Benjamin Moore, Moores Clothing For Men, Cazza Petite, Quesada, Norms Pizza and First Choice Haircutters chose this outstanding location for their Dieppe stores. Property has pylon signage along Paul Street and great visibility from both Regis Street and Champlain Street due to its configuration close to the street. There is easy ingress and egress from Paul, Ste-Thérèse and Olivier Streets. There is a projected parking expansion and pedestrian sidewalk on Olivier Street, which will bring the total parking available to ± 114 spaces.

525 Regis is conveniently location in Dieppe Shopping District, a rapidly growing area. The site is easily accessed from Highway 15 and is just a short drive to Downtown Dieppe and Downtown Moncton. The property exceptional exposure and positioning along Regis Street allows it to easily service the community. Some other highlights include ample parking spaces, excellent signage opportunities, high ceilings and lots of natural light throughout. Check out the flyer for more!
